This article is a presidential proclamation by Barack Obama declaring March 3 through March 9, 2013, as National Consumer Protection Week. The proclamation highlights the financial crisis that occurred over four years ago and emphasizes the need for regulations to protect Americans from irresponsible actions. The Obama Administration has taken steps to ramp up consumer protection, including establishing a unit to combat fraud, launching campaigns to help students make smart decisions about college payments, cracking down on unscrupulous lenders and credit card companies, and providing resources for managing finances and safeguarding against identity theft. The proclamation calls for clear rules, fair treatment, and full disclosure for consumers in various financial transactions. The President urges government officials, industry leaders, and advocates to share information about consumer protection and educate citizens about their rights.